{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875055269,"sessionID":"ses_2859954bcffewV0OdP2X4fAZVs","part":{"id":"prt_d7a66da99001XVCrlifQIFKtle","messageID":"msg_d7a66ccd6001SpySqpqvTgEVt0","sessionID":"ses_2859954bcffewV0OdP2X4fAZVs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_590784ee54a24890971bef93","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n2: \n3: **Module:** manifests  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** L  \n6: **Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Chart Structure & Metadata\n11: \n12: - [ ] **T001** Create directory `manifests/charts/base/`\n13: - [ ] **T002** Create `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` with apiVersion=v2, name=agentcube, version=0.1.0, appVersion=1.0.0\n14: - [ ] **T003** Create `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` with all documented keys (redis, workloadmanager, router, volcano)\n15: - [ ] **T004** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/` directory\n16: - [ ] **T005** Create `manifests/charts/base/crds/` directory\n17: - [ ] **T006** Verify `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## Phase 2: Helper Templates\n22: \n23: - [ ] **T010** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` with workloadmanager fullname template\n24: - [ ] **T011** Add router fullname template to `_helpers.tpl`\n25: - [ ] **T012** Add workloadmanager labels template to `_helpers.tpl`\n26: - [ ] **T013** Add router labels template to `_helpers.tpl`\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## Phase 3: CRD Manifests\n31: \n32: - [ ] **T020** Add AgentRuntime CRD to `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n33: - [ ] **T021** Add CodeInterpreter CRD to `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`\n34: - [ ] **T022** Verify CRDs are valid Kubernetes manifests\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## Phase 4: Workload Manager\n39: \n40: - [ ] **T030** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` Service (ClusterIP, port 8080)\n41: - [ ] **T031** Create Workload Manager Deployment template with replicas from values\n42: - [ ] **T032** Configure Workload Manager image (repository, tag, pullPolicy) from values\n43: - [ ] **T033** Add REDIS_ADDR env var from `.Values.redis.addr`\n44: - [ ] **T034** Add REDIS_PASSWORD env var from `.Values.redis.password`\n45: - [ ] **T035** Add AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE env var from `.Release.Namespace`\n46: - [ ] **T036** Configure livenessProbe GET /health\n47: - [ ] **T037** Configure readinessProbe GET /health\n48: - [ ] **T038** Configure resources (limits/requests cpu/memory) from values\n49: - [ ] **T039** Add extraEnv support from `.Values.workloadmanager.extraEnv`\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## Phase 5: Router\n54: \n55: - [ ] **T050** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` Service\n56: - [ ] **T051** Configure Router Service type from values (default ClusterIP)\n57: - [ ] **T052** Configure Router Service port and targetPort from values\n58: - [ ] **T053** Create Router Deployment with replicas from values\n59: - [ ] **T054** Configure Router image from values\n60: - [ ] **T055** Add WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var (internal DNS)\n61: - [ ] **T056** Add REDIS_ADDR env var from values\n62: - [ ] **T057** Add REDIS_PASSWORD env var from values\n63: - [ ] **T058** Add --debug arg when `.Values.router.debug` is true\n64: - [ ] **T059** Configure livenessProbe GET /health/live\n65: - [ ] **T060** Configure readinessProbe GET /health/ready\n66: - [ ] **T061** Configure Router resources from values\n67: - [ ] **T062** Add Router extraEnv support\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## Phase 6: Workload Manager RBAC\n72: \n73: - [ ] **T070** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n74: - [ ] **T071** Create workloadmanager ServiceAccount\n75: - [ ] **T072** Create workloadmanager ClusterRole with all required rules (agents.x-k8s.io, extensions.agents.x-k8s.io, runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh, core pods/secrets, tokenreviews)\n76: - [ ] **T073** Create workloadmanager ClusterRoleBinding\n77: - [ ] **T074** Verify RBAC template renders correctly\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## Phase 7: Router RBAC (Optional)\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T080** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/router.yaml`\n84: - [ ] **T081** Add conditional rendering based on `.Values.router.rbac.create`\n85: - [ ] **T082** Create router ServiceAccount (with default name)\n86: - [ ] **T083** Create router Role with secret permissions\n87: - [ ] **T084** Create router RoleBinding\n88: - [ ] **T085** Verify RBAC is NOT rendered when `router.rbac.create: false`\n89: - [ ] **T086** Verify RBAC IS rendered when `router.rbac.create: true`\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## Phase 8: Volcano Scheduler (Optional)\n94: \n95: - [ ] **T090** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano/agent-scheduler.yaml`\n96: - [ ] **T091** Add conditional rendering based on `.Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled`\n97: - [ ] **T092** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ServiceAccount\n98: - [ ] **T093** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ConfigMap\n99: - [ ] **T094** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ClusterRole\n100: - [ ] **T095** Create volcano-agent-scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n101: - [ ] **T096** Create volcano-agent-scheduler Service\n102: - [ ] **T097** Create volcano-agent-scheduler Deployment with configurable replicas/image\n103: - [ ] **T098** Verify Volcano resources are NOT rendered when disabled\n104: - [ ] **T099** Verify Volcano resources ARE rendered when enabled\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## Phase 9: Validation & Testing\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T100** Run `helm lint manifests/charts/base` - must pass\n111: - [ ] **T101** Run `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=redis:6379` - must succeed\n112: - [ ] **T102** Verify Workload Manager Service in rendered output\n113: - [ ] **T103** Verify Router Service in rendered output\n114: - [ ] **T104** Verify ClusterRole with correct rules in output\n115: - [ ] **T105** Verify conditional Router RBAC renders correctly (rbac.create=true)\n116: - [ ] **T106** Verify conditional Volcano renders correctly (scheduler.enabled=true)\n117: - [ ] **T107** Run full render with all options and verify no errors\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## Phase 10: Documentation & Cleanup\n122: \n123: - [ ] **T110** Add README.md to chart with basic usage instructions\n124: - [ ] **T111** Verify all file permissions are correct (644)\n125: - [ ] **T112** Ensure no hardcoded values (all from values.yaml or helpers)\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## Dependencies\n130: \n131: ```\n132: T001 → T002 → T003 → T004 → T005 → T006\n133: T010 → T013 (depends on T002)\n134: T020, T021 (can parallel)\n135: T030-T039 (Workload Manager - sequential within phase)\n136: T050-T062 (Router - sequential within phase)\n137: T070-T074 (RBAC - sequential)\n138: T080-T086 (Router RBAC - depends on T070-T074)\n139: T090-T099 (Volcano - can parallel after T091)\n140: T100-T107 (Testing - depends on all templates)\n141: T110-T112 (Doc - can parallel after T100)\n142: ```\n143: \n144: **Parallel:** Phase 3 (CRDs) can be done in parallel with Phase 4-5 (Workload Manager & Router)\n145: \n146: ## Acceptance Criteria\n147: \n148: - [ ] Chart.yaml with name=agentcube, version=0.1.0 passes `helm lint`\n149: - [ ] values.yaml contains all documented keys (redis, workloadmanager, router, volcano)\n150: - [ ] Helm template renders without error: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=redis:6379`\n151: - [ ] Workload Manager Deployment and Service rendered\n152: - [ ] Router Deployment and Service rendered\n153: - [ ] Workload Manager ClusterRole with required rules\n154: - [ ] Router RBAC conditional (create=false: not rendered, create=true: rendered)\n155: - [ ] Volcano scheduler conditional (enabled=false: not rendered, enabled=true: rendered)\n156: - [ ] CRDs present in crds/ directory\n157: - [ ] All environment variables (REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD, WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE) in templates\n158: \n159: ## Verification Commands\n160: \n161: ```bash\n162: # Lint check\n163: helm lint manifests/charts/base\n164: \n165: # Basic template render\n166: helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=redis:6379\n167: \n168: # Full render with optional components\n169: helm template test manifests/charts/base \\\n170:   --set redis.addr=redis:6379 \\\n171:   --set redis.password=secret \\\n172:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n173:   --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true\n174: ```\n175: \n176: **Module:** pkg/apis  \n177: **Language:** Go  \n178: **Size:** S  \n179: **Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n180: \n181: ---\n182: \n183: ## Tasks\n184: \n185: - [ ] **T1** Define `CodeInterpreter` CRD type struct with embedded TypeMeta and ObjectMeta  \n186:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n187:   - Verify: Type struct includes `Spec` and `Status` fields with appropriate JSON tags\n188: \n189: - [ ] **T2** Add kubebuilder markers for CodeInterpreter  \n190:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n191:   - Markers: `+genclient`, `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:resource:shortName=ci`  \n192:   - Verify: Markers present above type definition\n193: \n194: - [ ] **T3** Define `CodeInterpreterList` list type  \n195:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n196:   - Verify: List type embeds TypeMeta, ListMeta and contains `Items []CodeInterpreter`\n197: \n198: - [ ] **T4** Define `CodeInterpreterSpec` spec struct  \n199:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n200:   - Fields: AuthMode, MaxSessionDuration, SessionTimeout, Ports, Template, WarmPoolSize  \n201:   - Verify: All fields with appropriate kubebuilder validation markers\n202: \n203: - [ ] **T5** Define `CodeInterpreterStatus` status struct  \n204:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n205:   - Fields: Conditions, ObservedGeneration, Ready  \n206:   - Verify: Status struct follows standard Kubernetes status pattern\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T6** Define `AuthMode` enum type and constants  \n209:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n210:   - Constants: `AuthModePicod = \"picod\"`, `AuthModeNone = \"none\"`  \n211:   - Verify: Enum with +kubebuilder:validation:Enum marker\n212: \n213: - [ ] **T7** Define `ContainerTemplateSpec` supporting type  \n214:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`  \n215:   - Fields: Image, Command, Args, Env, Resources, RuntimeClassName  \n216:   - Verify: Required Image field with proper markers\n217: \n218: - [ ] **T8** Add CodeInterpreter types to register.go  \n219:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`  \n220:   - Add `&CodeInterpreter{}` and `&CodeInterpreterList{}` to AddKnownTypes  \n221:   - Verify: Both types registered in scheme\n222: \n223: - [ ] **T9** Generate DeepCopy methods  \n224:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`  \n225:   - Use: `controller-gen object paths=./pkg/apis/...`  \n226:   - Verify: DeepCopyInto and DeepCopy methods generated for all types\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T10** Write unit tests for CodeInterpreter types  \n229:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go`  \n230:   - Coverage: Type instantiation, DeepCopy, defaults validation  \n231:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` passes\n232: \n233: - [ ] **T11** Verify types compile correctly  \n234:   - Command: `go build ./pkg/apis/...`  \n235:   - Verify: No compilation errors\n236: \n237: - [ ] **T12** Run linter on API types  \n238:   - Command: `golangci-lint run ./pkg/apis/...` or `go vet ./pkg/apis/...`  \n239:   - Verify: No linting errors\n240: \n241: ---\n242: \n243: ## Dependencies\n244: \n245: ```\n246: T1 → T2 → T3 → T4 → T5 → T6 → T7 → T8 → T9 → T10 → T11 → T12\n247: ```\n248: \n249: **Parallel:** T6, T7 can be done in parallel with T4, T5\n250: \n251: ## Acceptance Criteria\n252: \n253: - [ ] CodeInterpreter CRD type defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n254: - [ ] CodeInterpreter includes spec: authMode, maxSessionDuration, sessionTimeout, ports, template, warmPoolSize\n255: - [ ] CodeInterpreter includes status: conditions, observedGeneration, ready\n256: - [ ] All types implement `runtime.Object` interface\n257: - [ ] DeepCopy methods generated and compile correctly\n258: - [ ] `go build ./pkg/apis/...` passes\n259: - [ ] `go vet ./pkg/apis/...` passes\n260: - [ ] Unit tests pass\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: # AR-003: CRD 共享类型与常量\n265: \n266: **Module:** pkg/apis  \n267: **Language:** Go  \n268: **Size:** S  \n269: **Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ## Tasks\n274: \n275: - [ ] **T1** 定义 `TargetPort` 共享结构体（端口配置）\n276:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n277:   - 字段: Port, Protocol, Name, PathPrefix\n278:   - 验证: 类型定义正确，JSON tag 完整\n279: \n280: - [ ] **T2** 定义 `PodTemplateSpec` 共享结构体（Pod 模板）\n281:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n282:   - 验证: 嵌入 metav1.ObjectMeta，可选 Spec 引用 PodSpec\n283: \n284: - [ ] **T3** 定义 `PodSpec` 共享结构体（Pod 规范子集）\n285:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n286:   - 字段: Containers, Volumes, RestartPolicy, ServiceAccountName, NodeSelector, Affinity, Tolerations 等\n287:   - 验证: 所有字段正确从 corev1.PodSpec 引用\n288: \n289: - [ ] **T4** 定义 `ContainerSpec` 共享结构体（容器规范子集）\n290:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n291:   - 字段: Name, Image, Command, Args, Env, Resources, Ports 等\n292:   - 验证: 包含容器核心字段\n293: \n294: - [ ] **T5** 定义 `AuthMode` 类型及常量\n295:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n296:   - 常量: `AuthModePicod = \"picod\"`, `AuthModeNone = \"none\"`\n297:   - 验证: 类型定义和常量值正确\n298: \n299: - [ ] **T6** 为 TargetPort 添加 kubebuilder 验证标记\n300:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n301:   - 验证: Port 范围 1-65535, Protocol 枚举 HTTP/HTTPS\n302: \n303: - [ ] **T7** 为 PodSpec 字段添加可选标记\n304:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n305:   - 验证: 所有字段标记 +optional\n306: \n307: - [ ] **T8** 为 ContainerSpec 字段添加验证标记\n308:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n309:   - 验证: Name 和 Image 标记为 required\n310: \n311: - [ ] **T9** 运行 deep copy 生成\n312:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n313:   - 命令: `controller-gen object paths=./pkg/apis/...`\n314:   - 验证: 所有共享类型的 DeepCopy 方法已生成\n315: \n316: - [ ] **T10** 验证共享类型编译正确\n317:   - 命令: `go build ./pkg/apis/...`\n318:   - 验证: 无编译错误\n319: \n320: - [ ] **T11** 运行 linter 检查\n321:   - 命令: `go vet ./pkg/apis/...`\n322:   - 验证: 无 lint 错误\n323: \n324: - [ ] **T12** 编写共享类型单元测试\n325:   - File: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go`\n326:   - 验证: `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` 通过\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ## 依赖关系\n331: \n332: ```\n333: T1 ─┬─> T6 ─> T9 ─> T10 ─> T11 ─> T12\n334: T2 ─┤\n335: T3 ─┤\n336: T4 ─┤\n337: T5 ─┘\n338: T7 ─> T9\n339: T8 ─> T9\n340: ```\n341: \n342: **并行:** T2, T3, T4, T5 可并行执行\n343: \n344: ## 验收标准\n345: \n346: - [ ] TargetPort, PodTemplateSpec, PodSpec, ContainerSpec 共享类型已定义\n347: - [ ] AuthMode 类型及常量已定义\n348: - [ ] 所有类型包含正确的 kubebuilder 验证标记\n349: - [ ] DeepCopy 方法已生成并编译正确\n350: - [ ] `go build ./pkg/apis/...` 通过\n351: - [ ] `go vet ./pkg/apis/...` 通过\n352: - [ ] 单元测试通过\n353: \n354: ---\n355: \n356: # AR-008: Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 (Sandbox GC Timing Cleanup Mechanism)\n357: \n358: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n359: **Language:** Go  \n360: **Size:** S  \n361: **Design Stage:** ST-3 completed (design in `pkg/workloadmanager/design.md`)\n362: \n363: ---\n364: \n365: ## Tasks\n366: \n367: ### Phase 1: Core Data Structures\n368: \n369: - [ ] **T-001** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/gc.go` with GCConfig struct (Interval, BatchSize, MaxConcurrentDeletes, GracePeriod, EnableMetrics)\n370: - [ ] **T-002** Implement DefaultGCConfig() function with sensible defaults (5m interval, 50 batch, 10 concurrent, 30s grace)\n371: - [ ] **T-003** Create GCWorker struct with client, k8sClient, config, stopCh, cleanupMgr, expirationChecker fields\n372: - [ ] **T-004** Implement GCResult struct (ScannedCount, ExpiredCount, DeletedCount, FailedCount, Duration, Errors)\n373: - [ ] **T-005** Implement GCStats struct (TotalCycles, TotalDeleted, TotalFailed, LastRunTime, LastResult)\n374: \n375: ### Phase 2: GC Worker Core\n376: \n377: - [ ] **T-006** Implement NewGCWorker() constructor function\n378: - [ ] **T-007** Implement GCWorker.Start(ctx) with ticker-based scheduling\n379: - [ ] **T-008** Implement GCWorker.Stop() method\n380: - [ ] **T-009** Implement GCWorker.runGCCycle() - main GC cycle logic\n381: - [ ] **T-010** Implement GCWorker.getNamespaces() to list target namespaces\n382: - [ ] **T-011** Implement GCWorker.processNamespace() to scan and delete expired resources in a namespace\n383: \n384: ### Phase 3: Expiration Detection & Deletion\n385: \n386: - [ ] **T-012** Implement GCWorker.isExpired(*AgentRuntime) using expiration.go logic\n387: - [ ] **T-013** Implement GCWorker.isExpired(*CodeInterpreter) using expiration.go logic\n388: - [ ] **T-014** Implement GCWorker.getLastActivityTime() to extract from annotations\n389: - [ ] **T-015** Implement GCWorker.deleteAgentRuntime() with CleanupManager integration\n390: - [ ] **T-016** Implement GCWorker.deleteCodeInterpreter() with CleanupManager integration\n391: \n392: ### Phase 4: HTTP API Integration\n393: \n394: - [ ] **T-017** Implement GCServer wrapper struct\n395: - [ ] **T-018** Implement GCTriggerResponse, GCStatusResponse, GCConfigUpdateRequest types\n396: - [ ] **T-019** Implement NewGCServer() constructor\n397: - [ ] **T-020** Implement GCServer.RegisterRoutes() with /gc/* endpoints\n398: - [ ] **T-021** Implement handleTrigger() - POST /api/v1/gc/trigger\n399: - [ ] **T-022** Implement handleStatus() - GET /api/v1/gc/status\n400: - [ ] **T-023** Implement handleConfigUpdate() - PUT /api/v1/gc/config\n401: \n402: ### Phase 5: Configuration & Integration\n403: \n404: - [ ] **T-024** Add GCConfig to server Config struct\n405: - [ ] **T-025** Load GC config from environment variables (GC_INTERVAL, GC_BATCH_SIZE, GC_MAX_CONCURRENT_DELETES, GC_GRACE_PERIOD, GC_ENABLED)\n406: - [ ] **T-026** Initialize and start GC worker in server startup\n407: - [ ] **T-027** Register GC routes in server router setup\n408: \n409: ### Phase 6: Testing\n410: \n411: - [ ] **T-028** Create `pkg/workloadmanager/gc_test.go`\n412: - [ ] **T-029** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerIsExpired_* (with DeletionTimestamp, TTL, idle timeout)\n413: - [ ] **T-030** Write unit test: TestGCConfig validation\n414: - [ ] **T-031** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerGetNamespaces\n415: - [ ] **T-032** Write unit test: TestGCWorkerStartStop\n416: - [ ] **T-033** Write unit test: TestGCServerRoutes\n417: \n418: ### Phase 7: Documentation & Cleanup\n419: \n420: - [ ] **T-034** Add error variables (ErrGCWorkerNotRunning, ErrGCAlreadyRunning, ErrInvalidConfig)\n421: - [ ] **T-035** Add logging at appropriate levels (V(4) cycle, V(2) failures, V(1) config)\n422: - [ ] **T-036** Verify code compiles: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n423: - [ ] **T-037** Run tests: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v`\n424: - [ ] **T-038** Verify 80% test coverage for gc.go\n\n(End of file - total 424 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n**Module:** manifests  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Chart Structure & Metadata\n\n- [ ] **T001** Create directory `manifests/charts/base/`\n- [ ] **T002** Create `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` with apiVersion=v2, name=agentcube, version=0.1.0, appVersion=1.0.0\n- [ ] **T003** Create `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` with all documented keys (redis, workloadmanager, router, volcano)\n- [ ] **T004** Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/` directory\n- [ ] **T005** Create `manifests/charts/base/crds/` directory\n- [ ] **T006** Verify `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775875055244,"end":1775875055266}}}}
