ine 107: ## Scenario: Agentd Dockerfile\n  Line 109: ### AR-032-011: Agentd multi-stage build\n  Line 111: - **GIVEN** docker/Dockerfile.agentd\n  Line 117: ### AR-032-012: Agentd runtime configuration\n  Line 125: ### AR-032-013: Agentd image size\n  Line 136: ### AR-032-014: Build all images target\n  Line 143: ### AR-032-015: Individual build targets\n  Line 150: ### AR-032-016: Push targets\n  Line 157: ### AR-032-017: Image naming convention\n  Line 169: ### AR-032-018: Binary execution\n  Line 176: ### AR-032-019: Non-root execution\n  Line 183: ### AR-032-020: Multi-stage layers verification\n  Line 191: ### AR-032-021: Build cache reuse\n  Line 202: ### AR-032-022: Minimal runtime image\n  Line 209: ### AR-032-023: No sensitive data in image\n  Line 220: ### AR-032-024: Build context compatibility\n  Line 227: ### AR-032-025: Binary compatibility\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n  Line 5: Implement multi-stage Docker builds for AgentCube server components, consolidating from multiple separate Dockerfiles into 3 optimized container images: `agentcube-router`, `agentcube-workload-manager`, and `agentcube-agentd` (with `picod` sidecar option).\n  Line 21: Create consolidated Dockerfiles using multi-stage builds at `docker/`:\n  Line 32: - **Maintainability**: Single Dockerfile pattern per image type\n  Line 43: | Router Dockerfile | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Multi-stage build for router binary |\n  Line 44: | Workload Manager Dockerfile | `docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager` | Multi-stage build for workload-manager binary |\n  Line 45: | Agentd Dockerfile | `docker/Dockerfile.agentd` | Multi-stage build for agentd binary (includes picod option) |\n  Line 46: | Base build stage | `docker/base.Dockerfile` | Shared Go build environment |\n  Line 51: - Agent workspace Dockerfiles (already exists in `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n  Line 103: ### Option 2: Separate Dockerfiles per binary (Not Selected)\n  Line 126: ├── base.Dockerfile          # Shared Go build stage (builder)\n  Line 127: ├── Dockerfile.router        # Router: builder → alpine runtime\n  Line 128: ├── Dockerfile.workload-manager  # Workload Manager: builder → alpine runtime\n  Line 129: └── Dockerfile.agentd        # Agentd + Picod: builder → alpine runtime\n  Line 134: Each runtime Dockerfile follows this pattern:\n  Line 169: \tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router:latest .\n  Line 172: \tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager -t agentcube-workload-manager:latest .\n  Line 175: \tdocker build -f docker/Dockerfile.agentd -t agentcube-agentd:latest .\n  Line 199: - [ ] Create `docker/base.Dockerfile` for shared Go build environment\n  Line 201: ### Phase 2: Implement Router Dockerfile\n  Line 203: - [ ] Create `docker/Dockerfile.router` with multi-stage build\n  Line 207: ### Phase 3: Implement Workload Manager Dockerfile\n  Line 209: - [ ] Create `docker/Dockerfile.workload-manager`\n  Line 213: ### Phase 4: Implement Agentd Dockerfile\n  Line 215: - [ ] Create `docker/Dockerfile.agentd`\n  Line 237: | DOCKER-001 | Build router image | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router` succeeds, image ~25-30MB |\n  Line 253: | Router Dockerfile | 1 hour |\n  Line 254: | Workload Manager Dockerfile | 1 hour |\n  Line 255: | Agentd Dockerfile | 1 hour |\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md:\n  Line 83: - `docker/Dockerfile` — Workload Manager image build\n  Line 84: - `docker/Dockerfile.router` — Router image build\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md:\n  Line 75: Validates and prepares a workspace, merges CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generates a Dockerfile.\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 227 mat